{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Konstantinos Mavropanos | image = 17 Merci Arsène - Celebrating Kolasinac's goal (27086257377) (cropped).jpg | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Konstantinos Mavropanos<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/844127 |title=2018/19 Premier League squads confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=3 September 2018 |accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|12|11|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Athens]], Greece | height = 1.92 m | position = [[Centre back (association football)|Centre back]] | currentclub = [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] | clubnumber = 27 | youthyears1 = 2008–2016 | youthclubs1 = [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]] | years1 = 2016–2018 | clubs1 = [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]] | caps1 = 16 | goals1 = 3 | years2 = 2018– | clubs2 = [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] | caps2 = 4 | goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2017– | nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-21 football team|Greece U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 20:00, 3 February 2019 (UTC) | ntupdate = 21:39, 22 March 2018 (UTC) }} '''Konstantinos "Dinos" Mavropanos''' ({{lang-gr|Κωνσταντίνος "Ντίνος" Μαυροπάνος}}; born 11 December 1997) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Centre back (association football)|centre back]] for {{English football updater|Arsenal}} club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and for the [[Greece national under-21 football team]].<ref name=AFC>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/arsenal/players/konstantinos-mavropanos|title=Konstantinos Mavropanos|website=Arsenal.com}}</ref>
==Club career== ===PAS Giannina=== Born in Athens,<ref name="IG">{{cite news|last1=Mountney|first1=Dan|last2=Yousif|first2=Layth|title=Arsenal chief scout tells Wenger to sign £2m Greek starlet Konstantinos Mavropanos|url=http://www.islingtongazette.co.uk/sport/football/arsenal/arsenal-chief-scout-tells-wenger-to-sign-2m-greek-starlet-konstantinos-mavropanos-1-5341391|accessdate=4 January 2018|work=Islington Gazette|date=3 January 2018}}</ref> Mavropanos began his career with the youth side at [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]] where he stayed for eight years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Κωνσταντίνος Μαυροπάνος: Το νέο διαμάντι του ΠΑΣ Γιάννινα|url=http://www.gazzetta.gr/match-review/article/1126969/konstantinos-mayropanos-neo-diamanti-toy-pas-giannina-pics|accessdate=4 January 2018|work=Gazzetta}}</ref> He then joined [[Superleague Greece|Super League]] side [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]] in January 2016, signing a three-and-a-half year contract.<ref name="W">{{cite news|last1=Wheatley|first1=Chris|title=Who Is Arsenal Signing Mavropanos? Meet Greece's Next Big Defender|url=http://www.goal.com/en-au/news/who-is-arsenal-signing-mavropanos-meet-greeces-next-big/au4md3jrmok31ekngiks9arng|accessdate=4 January 2018|work=Goal.com|date=4 January 2018}}</ref> Mavropanos made his competitive debut for [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]] in the [[Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]] on 29 November 2016. He started and played the full match as [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]] won 1–0.<ref>{{cite web|title=Agrotikos 0-1 PAS Giannina|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2016/11/29/greece/cup/pmas-agrotikos-asteras-evosmou/pas-giannina/2361953/|website=Soccerway}}</ref>
Mavropanos made his league debut for PAS Giannina on 5 April 2017 against [[Veria F.C.|Veria]]. He started and played 57 minutes as PAS Giannina lost 3–0.<ref>{{cite web|title=Veria 3-0 PAS Giannina|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/04/05/greece/super-league/veria-fc/pas-giannina/2404090/|website=Soccerway}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 19 August 2017 during the first league match of the season against [[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripolis]]. His 19th-minute goal would be winner in a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|title=Asteras 1-2 PAS Giannina|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/19/greece/super-league/asteras-tripolis/pas-giannina/2560499/|website=Soccerway}}</ref> Mavropanos was then voted man of the match in PAS Giannina's draw against [[AEK Athens F.C.|ΑΕΚ Athens]] a week later on 27 August.<ref name="W"/>
Mavropanos made 23 times in all competitions for PAS Giannina, scoring three goals.<ref name=AFC />
===Arsenal=== On 4 January 2018, Mavropanos signed for [[Premier League]] side [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Konstantinos Mavropanos joins the club|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/konstantinos-mavropanos-joins-club|accessdate=4 January 2018|work=Arsenal Club|date=4 January 2018}}</ref> On 15 January, Mavropanos helped Arsenal U-23 beat Manchester United’s reserves 4–0 at home, playing the entire 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal U23 4-0 Manchester United U23: Konstantinos Mavropanos makes first appearance after January move as Jeff Reine-Adelaide shines in rout |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-5272441/Arsenal-U23-4-0-Manchester-United-U23-Match-report.html |accessdate=15 January 2018|website=Daily Mail Online}}</ref> On 2 February, Mavropanos was an addition to the [[Europa League]] squad for the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|knockout phase]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/913641/Arsenal-Europa-League-squad-Santi-Cazorla|title=Arsenal include shock name in Europa League squad: You'll never guess who Wenger picked|accessdate=2 February 2018|website=The Daily Express}}</ref> On 29 April, Mavropanos made his Premier League debut in a 2–1 defeat against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Old Trafford]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mavropanos makes his debut: Man Utd V Arsenal teams |url=https://news.arseblog.com/2018/04/mavropanos-makes-his-debut-man-utd-v-arsenal-teams/|accessdate=29 April 2018|date=29 April 2018}}</ref> His performance were praised by the fans and multiple pundits.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal lost at Man United but debutant Mavropanos earns 8/10 |url=http://global.espn.com/football/club/arsenal/359/blog/post/3477353/arsenal-debutant-konstantinos-mavropanos-earns-8-out-of-10-despite-defeat-at-man-united?src=com/|accessdate=30 April 2018|date=29 April 2018}}</ref> Mavropanos made his home debut in the club's next home match against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]]. The match was also the final home game under manager [[Arsène Wenger]], with Mavropanos keeping his first clean sheet as the team won 5–0.<ref>{{cite news|title= Arsenal 5–0 Burnley |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43939015|accessdate=9 May 2018|date=6 May 2018}}</ref> Mavropanos played in the following game away against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], but was sent off after 15 minutes to conclude his first season at Arsenal.<ref>{{cite news|title= Arsenal: Good thing Konstantinos Mavropanos got that out of the way |url=https://paininthearsenal.com/2018/05/11/arsenal-konstantinos-mavropanos-way/|accessdate=13 May 2018|date=9 May 2018}}</ref>
On the beginning of October 2018, Mavropanos faced a groin injury, and was out until mid-December.<ref>{{cite news|title= Injury Update: Petr may be better in a month |url=https://theshortfuse.sbnation.com/2018/10/2/17928782/arsenal-injury-update-petr-cech-ainsley-maitland-niles-emile-smith-rowe-mavropanos-premier-league |accessdate=13 October 2018|date=2 October 2018}}</ref> On 15 January 2019, Mavropanos returned to competitive action after nearly four months (117 days to be exact) but preached caution over rushing into [[Unai Emery]]'s first-team. Mavropanos completed 70 minutes of the U23s' 5–1 win over Manchester City before being substituted as had been agreed with the first-team setup prior to kick-off. On 3 February 2019, he made his debut for the [[2018-19 Premier League|2018–19 season]] as a substitute of [[Shkodran Mustafi]] in a 3–1 away loss against champions [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Man City 3-1 Arsenal highlights and reaction as Sergio Aguero hits hat-trick |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-arsenal-score-highlights-15773780 |accessdate=3 February 2019|date=3 February 2019}}</ref>
